<tr bgcolor="#dfdfdf">
<td valign="top" width="20%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="black" style="font-size: 11px"><b>Elidis</b>
<br>22 October 2003</font></td><td width="80%"><font><b>doubts and fears about your Publications Roster</b>
<br>
<p>Hi,<br>I am one of the older ED-Fans (since 1995) and I collected most of the books published from FASA.<p></p>Now, I see the trend comming that you combine different older books <br>and make some additions, to get a new version of it.<p></p>For example:<p></p>living room plans a revival of the Adepts Way sourcebook in 3 new books called " way of ....."<p></p>You are planning a new version of Adepts Way called Adepts Compendium.<p></p>Like that you are planning to republish the horror, creature and the denizens sourcebooks.<p></p>Or splitting of the core rulebook into the GM-Kompendium and Players Compendium with some<br>additions. I saw this in many different roleplaying systems before and the benefit for older players<br>was always minimal.<p></p>My biggest fear is, every books I will buy from you contains half old and half new content.<br>At one side I dont`t want to buy older articles from different books again and again.<p></p>On the other side, I am VERY interested in your new articles and I also want to support you<br>in reviving ED worldwide.<p></p>Can you solve this conflict for me ?<p></p>You should build up a new ED-Community, but PLEASE don`t forget the old one !!!<p></p>Regards<p></p>Elidis</p>
</font></td>
</tr>
